    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i'm looking at some transcripts for a new customer service rep position. Can u give me a quick summary for both of these people? i need to know how well they communicate their ideas and if they seem like a good fit for a professional office environment.\n\nCandidate A:\nInterviewer: Can you tell me about a time you dealt with a difficult customer?\nCandidate A: Certainly. In my previous role, I encountered a client who was quite frustrated because their shipment was delayed. I remained calm, listened to their concerns without interruption, and then explained the steps we were taking to resolve the issue. Eventually, the customer expressed appreciation for my assistance.\n\nCandidate B:\nInterviewer: Can you tell me about a time you dealt with a difficult customer?\nCandidate B: Yeah, for sure. In my last job, I had this customer who was real upset cause their delivery was late. I stayed calm, just listened to what they had to say without cutting them off, then i explained what we was doing to fix the situation. In the end, they was real appreciative of the help i gave them.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
